  - mondo_definition: Epidermolysis bullosa simplex with circinate migratory erythema (EBS-migr) is a basal subtype of epidermolysis bullosa simplex (EBS) characterized by belt-like areas of erythema with multiple vesicles and small blisters at the advancing edge of erythema.
  - umls_description: A basal subtype of epidermolysis bullosa simplex with manifestation of belt-like areas of erythema with multiple vesicles and small blisters at the advancing edge of erythema. Prevalence is unknown but 2 families have been reported to date. Onset of the disease is usually at birth. The lesions occur on the limbs and trunk and heal with brown pigmentation but no scarring. Extracutaneous involvement is absent. The disease is due to a specific mutation in the krt5 gene, encoding keratin 5. Transmission is autosomal dominant.
